Find the slope-intercept form of the equation of the line through the points (-1,2), (3,8). 
Y = Mx + B
Slope = M = (Y2 -Y1) / (X2 -X1) = (8-2) / (3+1) = (6/4) = (3/2);
Y = (3/2)x + B
2 = (3/2)(-1) + b
[2 = (-3/2) + b](2)
4 = -3 + 2b
7 = 2b
b = (7/2)
 
Y = (3/2)x + (7/2);

